/author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Icar.\">Icar.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">3</biblScope> </bibl>): Cleitorian (<bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Arc.\">Arc.</a></author> </bibl>) word acc. to <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ AB\">AB</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1096</biblScope></bibl>. </sense> <sense n=\"2\" id=\"n116150.1\" level=\"3\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">στεφάναι</foreign> is glossed by <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">αἱ τῶν βωμῶν ὠλέναι,</foreign> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hsch.\">Hsch.</a></author> </bibl> </sense> <sense n=\"3\" id=\"n116150.2\" level=\"3\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">mat, mattress,</tr_> <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">gloss on </abbr> Lat.<tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">torus</tr_> (which has these and other senses), <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Gloss.\">Gloss.</a></title_>: cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὠλήν, ὠλενοστρόφος.</foreign> (Lat. <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">ulna,</tr_> OHG. <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">elina,</tr_> O<bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ E.\">E.</a></author> </bibl> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">eln, el-bogi,</tr_> 'ell, elbow'; Goth. <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">aleina;</tr_> also Skt. <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">aratni/s,</tr_> OSlav. <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">lak[ucaron]t[icaron],</tr_> Lith. <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">uolektìs</tr_> (all <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">=</abbr> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">elbow</tr_> and <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">ell</tr_>); cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὠλλόν</foreign> and <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἄλαξ.